1
00:00:01,125 --> 00:00:02,875
You...

2
00:00:04,875 --> 00:00:06,375
Are you leaving?

3
00:00:15,417 --> 00:00:17,375
Do you want me to stay?

4
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:25,833
You can leave, but pay me back first.

5
00:00:25,958 --> 00:00:27,750
And don't forget every
cent of the interest.

6
00:00:31,708 --> 00:00:34,042
Hey, Wooju.

7
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,417
Yeah?

8
00:00:37,417 --> 00:00:42,458
When we're talking money, call me Boss.

9
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:09,750
Teach me how to sing.

10
00:01:09,875 --> 00:01:10,875
You play the piano?

11
00:01:10,958 --> 00:01:13,417
I can play anything after hearing it once.

12
00:01:34,417 --> 00:01:35,792
How is that possible?

13
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:39,333
Like I said, I just
hear it and I've got it.

14
00:01:42,792 --> 00:01:46,708
♪ Fly me to the moon ♪

15
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:52,000
♪ Let me play among the stars ♪

16
00:01:53,083 --> 00:01:56,542
♪ Let me see what spring is like ♪

17
00:01:56,667 --> 00:02:01,667
♪ On Jupiter and Mars ♪

18
00:02:03,417 --> 00:02:06,375
♪ In other words ♪

19
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:09,167
♪ Hold my hand ♪

20
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:16,250
♪ In other words ♪

21
00:02:16,375 --> 00:02:19,208
♪ Baby, kiss me ♪

22
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:27,458
♪ Fill my heart with song ♪

23
00:02:27,583 --> 00:02:32,833
♪ And let me sing forevermore ♪

24
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:37,333
♪ You are all I long for ♪

25
00:02:37,458 --> 00:02:42,375
♪ All I worship and adore ♪

26
00:02:43,792 --> 00:02:46,792
♪ In other words ♪

27
00:02:46,917 --> 00:02:51,708
♪ Please be true ♪

28
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:56,042
♪ In other words ♪

29
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:59,375
♪ I love you ♪

30
00:03:03,417 --> 00:03:04,875
Whoa!

31
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:09,250
You scared me.

32
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:12,333
Didn't I tell you I was a prince?

33
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:13,917
I did it again.

34
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,208
Stop talking nonsense.

35
00:03:22,167 --> 00:03:24,750
♪ Fly me to the moon ♪

36
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:28,625
♪ Let me play among the stars ♪

37
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:31,708
♪ Let me see what spring is like ♪

38
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:35,875
♪ On Jupiter and Mars ♪

39
00:03:36,667 --> 00:03:38,333
♪ In other words ♪

40
00:03:39,458 --> 00:03:43,667
♪ Hold my hand ♪

41
00:03:43,792 --> 00:03:49,750
♪ In other words ♪

42
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:53,333
♪ Baby, kiss me ♪

43
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:06,292
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

44
00:04:08,875 --> 00:04:10,333
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

45
00:04:12,792 --> 00:04:14,458
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

46
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:18,458
(Q / Q)

47
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:22,500
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

48
00:04:27,292 --> 00:04:32,083
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 7)

49
00:04:33,792 --> 00:04:34,792
(Fly Me to the Moon)

50
00:04:37,917 --> 00:04:40,417
Hachi, congratulations.

51
00:04:40,917 --> 00:04:42,167
Is it finally fixed?

52
00:04:42,292 --> 00:04:44,458
I think this device will be restored soon.

53
00:04:44,583 --> 00:04:47,125
Communication on Earth
will be possible tonight.

54
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:48,458
Oh.

55
00:04:51,542 --> 00:04:53,292
Will you be back soon?

56
00:04:53,917 --> 00:04:57,667
Yes, I can finally say goodbye
to this dump planet Earth.

57
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:00,750
I like Earth quite a bit.

58
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:01,875
Don't you?

59
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,417
Well...

60
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:04,875
Hachi.

61
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,792
I have something I wanna give you.

62
00:05:08,083 --> 00:05:10,958
A token of our friendship.

63
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,500
C'mon, let's try it on.

64
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:15,750
How should... how should I...?

65
00:05:15,875 --> 00:05:17,125
Look there.

66
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:18,750
I'll put it on you.

67
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:24,833
Wow.

68
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,292
It looks good on you.

69
00:05:27,417 --> 00:05:28,708
Thanks.

70
00:05:30,542 --> 00:05:33,125
Don't forget me when you go back home, OK?

71
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:39,542
By any chance... do you wanna go with me?

72
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:43,833
No, I have to stay with the princess.

73
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:46,250
She needs me.

74
00:05:49,375 --> 00:05:51,125
Hey, I'll see you soon, okay?

75
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:52,500
Okay.

76
00:05:57,042 --> 00:05:59,500
Did you learn to bake from my dad?

77
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:00,958
Yeah.

78
00:06:01,208 --> 00:06:06,292
I came here to see your dad.

79
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:09,375
Why did you want to see him?

80
00:06:10,792 --> 00:06:15,625
He was my only friend.

81
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:20,500
My family, and my mentor.

82
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:24,958
He always took such good care of me.

83
00:06:27,208 --> 00:06:33,167
But how could you not know he passed away?

84
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:38,792
We lost touch a long time ago.

85
00:06:40,667 --> 00:06:43,208
He just left a letter and vanished.

86
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:47,875
Went somewhere far away.

87
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:57,875
I only heard later that he got married.

88
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:03,167
How did you know I was his son?

89
00:07:12,542 --> 00:07:14,417
It was obvious the moment I saw you.

90
00:07:15,708 --> 00:07:17,875
You look exactly like him.

91
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:29,667
Why didn't you say so earlier?

92
00:07:29,792 --> 00:07:31,750
Would you have believed me?

93
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,708
Even if I told you now,

94
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:37,000
you still wouldn't believe me, right?

95
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:43,667
That's because you're
always saying weird things.

96
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:48,458
Your dad's soul must have brought me here.

97
00:07:50,417 --> 00:07:55,125
I missed him so much,

98
00:07:59,375 --> 00:08:01,083
that's how I found you.

99
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,000
What are you doing?

100
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:23,375
A kiss.

101
00:08:25,125 --> 00:08:26,292
A kiss?

102
00:08:26,417 --> 00:08:27,208
Yeah.

103
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,083
Who kisses like that?

104
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:32,792
Well...

105
00:08:33,625 --> 00:08:36,000
That's how we do it back home.

106
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:40,333
Hey, since you're on Earth now,

107
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,958
do it the Earth way.

108
00:09:28,042 --> 00:09:29,333
Officer Shin.

109
00:09:29,458 --> 00:09:29,917
Yes?

110
00:09:30,042 --> 00:09:31,542
The report on last night's case,

111
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:32,708
is it finished?

112
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:34,083
Just a second.

113
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,333
Here it is.

114
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,292
Officer Shin.

115
00:09:42,417 --> 00:09:43,542
Yes, sir?

116
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:48,208
That... UFO... alien-related club,

117
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,667
did you quit it?

118
00:09:49,958 --> 00:09:53,208
Yes. I decided to drop any hobbies that

119
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:54,333
interfere with work.

120
00:09:54,375 --> 00:09:56,292
Okay, good. That's better.

121
00:09:56,417 --> 00:09:58,000
That's the way.

122
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:18,792
A little lower here.

123
00:10:18,917 --> 00:10:20,083
Ugh...

124
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:23,375
Hurry up!

125
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:24,583
Ouch.

126
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,667
Seriously.

127
00:10:28,875 --> 00:10:29,375
Hey...

128
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,208
Turn around.

129
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:34,875
Wait.

130
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,958
Oh, for heaven's sake.

131
00:10:47,125 --> 00:10:48,333
He's coming.

132
00:10:51,458 --> 00:10:53,083
Mina, trust me on this.

133
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:59,000
I bought this for my
partner, but you take it.

134
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:00,583
Why? We haven't even left yet.

135
00:11:00,708 --> 00:11:03,208
I'll explain later. Just put it on.

136
00:11:04,458 --> 00:11:05,667
What's with the sunglasses?

137
00:11:05,792 --> 00:11:09,125
I was in the dark for too
long. My eyes are sensitive.

138
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,208
Has anything been inconvenient lately?

139
00:11:11,326 --> 00:11:12,033
Of course it has...

140
00:11:12,064 --> 00:11:14,167
Not at all! You've taken
such good care of us.

141
00:11:14,292 --> 00:11:15,167
Everything's been fine.

142
00:11:15,292 --> 00:11:17,708
Hmm... I've been thinking.

143
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:20,750
And I'm curious how much you actually know.

144
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:24,792
You're aliens, aren't you?

145
00:11:26,208 --> 00:11:27,792
What about it?

146
00:11:27,917 --> 00:11:30,458
Are you here to arrest me? I
haven't done anything wrong.

147
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:31,708
What law did I break?

148
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,500
I'm a legal citizen here.

149
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:36,792
And I run a legitimate business.

150
00:11:36,917 --> 00:11:40,417
What is your real purpose on Earth?

151
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:44,583
Secretary Lee.

152
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:46,083
Yes, Chairman.

153
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,792
Oh my god! Run!

154
00:12:07,917 --> 00:12:09,250
Hurry... damn it.

155
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:15,167
(Operation: Alien Extermination)

156
00:12:18,875 --> 00:12:21,708
Is this where Woo-hyuk grew up?

157
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:24,083
Yes, I grew up here.

158
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:29,500
I had lots of friends, and the
director took care of me like a mother.

159
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:30,917
Woo-hyuk.

160
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:34,333
- Hello, Director.
- Oh, come on in.

161
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:37,042
- How have you been?
- Oh, thanks for coming all this way.

162
00:12:46,292 --> 00:12:49,052
(Operation: Alien Extermination)
Here is the list of confirmed aliens.

163
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:50,500
Wow, there are so many.

164
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:51,792
Yes, and...

165
00:12:52,417 --> 00:12:54,042
The aliens' first target

166
00:12:54,167 --> 00:12:57,292
is to activate the device inside
the Wooju Bakery building.

167
00:12:57,417 --> 00:12:58,809
What do you mean, activate the building?

168
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:00,708
It looks like an ordinary building,

169
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:05,083
but it's actually a
special device for aliens.

170
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:06,083
Wait, hold on.
What's wrong?

171
00:13:07,167 --> 00:13:07,792
Officer Sin.

172
00:13:07,917 --> 00:13:09,500
We shouldn't be handling this alone.

173
00:13:09,625 --> 00:13:13,792
Should we get the other
officers to look at this?

174
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:16,125
Ah...

175
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:18,542
Your mother seems like a wonderful person.

176
00:13:22,583 --> 00:13:26,583
I've never called her 'mother', though.

177
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:29,042
Woo-hyuk.

178
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,458
Do you think love is only about giving?

179
00:13:35,667 --> 00:13:37,458
Accepting love is also a form of love.

180
00:13:45,542 --> 00:13:46,875
Hmm?

181
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:48,625
Officer Shin.

182
00:13:49,375 --> 00:13:51,000
I'm off today, though.

183
00:13:51,125 --> 00:13:52,125
Hey, senior.

184
00:13:52,167 --> 00:13:54,500
Please, listen to my troubles.

185
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:55,667
What?

186
00:13:55,792 --> 00:13:57,000
Today...

187
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:59,875
is the most important day of my life.

188
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,750
- It's so hot.
- No, that's not it.

189
00:14:01,875 --> 00:14:03,434
I was supposed to go to the movies today.

190
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:04,583
Can't we do this tomorrow?

191
00:14:04,708 --> 00:14:06,292
Or you can just tell me over the phone.

192
00:14:06,417 --> 00:14:10,417
No, I need to see you in
person and tell you myself.

193
00:14:10,542 --> 00:14:12,917
Please, as a favor to your junior.

194
00:14:13,708 --> 00:14:15,917
Please, just listen.

195
00:14:16,458 --> 00:14:18,292
Fine, I'm on my way.

196
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:28,625
Chairman, Officer Lee is furious.
He wants to wipe them all out.

197
00:14:29,125 --> 00:14:30,445
Secretary Lee, what do you think?

198
00:14:30,542 --> 00:14:31,917
I agree.

199
00:14:32,042 --> 00:14:34,708
I don't think there's any
reason to keep them around.

200
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:39,500
The old owner of that bakery...

201
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:40,792
What about him?

202
00:14:40,917 --> 00:14:43,042
How did he end up on Earth?

203
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:45,958
Do you, perhaps, know?

204
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:47,750
What do you mean by that...

205
00:14:47,875 --> 00:14:50,333
He was the closest person to the King.

206
00:14:50,458 --> 00:14:53,125
Why would he flee to Earth?

207
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:57,250
How should I know that information?

208
00:14:57,375 --> 00:14:58,958
I'll be taking my leave.

209
00:15:09,125 --> 00:15:12,458
There's still... the accomplices and
the next steps for the investigation.

210
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:13,583
I'll report back to you.

211
00:15:13,708 --> 00:15:17,208
So you're saying aliens came to
Earth to harvest vital resources?

212
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,809
And they're still plotting a conspiracy?

213
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:22,667
And the leader of these
aliens is Lee Seong-yong?

214
00:15:22,792 --> 00:15:24,875
Yes, that's right...

215
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,125
Are you really expecting
us to believe this?

216
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:28,292
It's all true!

217
00:15:28,417 --> 00:15:30,958
Officer Shin and I risked
our lives to uncover this.

218
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:32,417
I'm not making this up.

219
00:15:32,542 --> 00:15:36,750
Do you think I can I apply
for witness protection?

220
00:15:38,208 --> 00:15:40,167
You just said you were
an alien, didn't you?

221
00:15:40,292 --> 00:15:41,625
Uh...

222
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:45,625
The laws of the Republic of Korea
mandate full witness protection.

223
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,500
Ah...

224
00:15:46,625 --> 00:15:48,500
I'll handle it.

225
00:15:52,125 --> 00:15:53,250
Senior.

226
00:15:53,375 --> 00:15:56,042
You don't actually believe him, do you?

227
00:15:56,167 --> 00:16:01,000
Woo-hyuk, don't worry. I'll just
shoot him and be done with it.

228
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:08,500
Senior.

229
00:16:09,292 --> 00:16:10,458
What's wrong with you?

230
00:16:10,583 --> 00:16:14,708
I believe everything Officer Shin found.

231
00:16:16,292 --> 00:16:19,958
And I believe this alien witness, too.

232
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,958
Because I'm an alien as well.

233
00:16:31,875 --> 00:16:36,542
Do we really have to use a cart
to move something this high-tech?

234
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:39,917
The Chairman is rushing us,
so we have to get it there fast.

235
00:16:41,958 --> 00:16:44,875
That's strange. Why is this
cart so hard to push today?

236
00:16:51,625 --> 00:16:54,167
Hey! Get out of here, you jerk!

237
00:16:54,292 --> 00:16:54,833
Get lost!

238
00:16:54,958 --> 00:16:55,958
Move it.

239
00:16:56,083 --> 00:16:56,875
Get out of the way.

240
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,417
Move.

241
00:16:58,542 --> 00:16:59,542
Get out now!

242
00:17:03,292 --> 00:17:06,583
Wow, this smells just like home.

243
00:17:06,708 --> 00:17:08,208
Hey, try some.

244
00:17:08,625 --> 00:17:09,625
Ah...

245
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:11,559
This is the first time I've
smelled a scent like home, boss.

246
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:15,000
Sir, the bread must be
paid for before eating.

247
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:17,708
Here.

248
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:24,292
Sir, this is too much.

249
00:17:24,417 --> 00:17:26,792
Keep it all. No need for change.

250
00:17:26,917 --> 00:17:28,958
Boss, why did you give him so much?

251
00:17:29,083 --> 00:17:31,875
We won't be needing Earth
money for much longer anyway.

252
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:32,875
That makes sense.

253
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,750
Yeah, Earth was never really
a place for us to stay anyway...

254
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:37,167
Good grief.

255
00:17:37,292 --> 00:17:38,625
Where's the owner of this place?

256
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:39,292
Our boss?

257
00:17:39,417 --> 00:17:41,667
I'm the owner. What's going on here?

258
00:17:41,792 --> 00:17:43,042
The owner?

259
00:17:45,375 --> 00:17:46,500
You're the owner here?

260
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:48,333
It's true, I'm the owner.

261
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,583
Are you crazy...

262
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,333
You're the owner?

263
00:17:53,458 --> 00:17:56,458
I mean... I work hard
like I'm the owner here.

264
00:17:56,958 --> 00:17:58,333
Are you the owner here?

265
00:17:58,458 --> 00:17:59,498
Yes... is there a problem?

266
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:01,833
We're taking over this building.

267
00:18:01,958 --> 00:18:04,667
I happen to have a much
bigger and nicer place nearby.

268
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:08,667
I can help you move there. And
there're issues about moving, right?

269
00:18:08,792 --> 00:18:10,667
We'll even cover the moving costs.

270
00:18:10,792 --> 00:18:12,083
We'll take care of everything.

271
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:13,934
How about it? That's a
pretty good deal, right?

272
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:14,792
So, Prince.

273
00:18:14,917 --> 00:18:16,458
We done being slaves here, too.

274
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:18,625
Wooju, let's sell this place.

275
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:20,917
Let's open a shop in a bigger place.

276
00:18:21,042 --> 00:18:22,333
No.

277
00:18:22,458 --> 00:18:23,875
Why not?

278
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:29,958
The landlord is here, too.

279
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:34,583
Grandpa, do we really have to move?

280
00:18:36,417 --> 00:18:37,833
Sigh...

281
00:18:37,958 --> 00:18:39,875
It seems it would be better to move.

282
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,417
How can that be?

283
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:44,770
The reason I opened this bakery
here is because of my father...

284
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:47,250
I just wanted to keep
my father's bakery going.

285
00:18:47,375 --> 00:18:49,333
You're the son of the
owner of the old bakery?

286
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:51,875
Then get out of here right now, you brat.

287
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,059
There's no reason for a father and son to stay
in the same place and die together, right?

288
00:18:54,083 --> 00:18:55,583
Are you threatening me?

289
00:18:55,708 --> 00:18:56,792
What threat?

290
00:18:56,917 --> 00:18:58,434
Who threatens someone by
offering them a huge pile of cash?

291
00:18:58,458 --> 00:19:00,018
And begging you to move?
You call that a threat?

292
00:19:00,042 --> 00:19:01,333
See that?

293
00:19:01,458 --> 00:19:05,458
My brother is a police officer.
I'm calling him right now.

294
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:13,333
But Chairman, why are
we keeping them alive?

295
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:16,167
In my opinion...

296
00:19:16,292 --> 00:19:19,932
Just like before, we should just make it look
like an accident and finish them off cleanly.

297
00:19:31,042 --> 00:19:32,101
This is your brother calling.

298
00:19:32,125 --> 00:19:36,833
If you run your mouth, everyone
here will die. Understand?

299
00:19:37,250 --> 00:19:38,000
Hyung?

300
00:19:38,125 --> 00:19:39,500
I'm a bit busy right now.

301
00:19:39,625 --> 00:19:42,708
I'll come over as soon
as I'm done. Don't worry.

302
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:44,000
Hyung?

303
00:19:50,208 --> 00:19:51,833
What did he say?

304
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:56,625
I've been a police officer on Earth
and lived a quiet life for a long time.

305
00:19:56,750 --> 00:19:59,101
I even received an award from the
Commissioner of the Police Agency.

306
00:19:59,125 --> 00:20:00,917
Secretary Lee.

307
00:20:01,375 --> 00:20:03,215
Are we just going to
leave these people alone?

308
00:20:03,292 --> 00:20:05,708
Just do as the Chairman says.

309
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:07,667
Sigh...

310
00:20:07,792 --> 00:20:12,417
If they run away, it's going
to be a headache for me.

311
00:20:12,542 --> 00:20:17,000
Forget it. The machine will
be activated soon anyway.

312
00:20:17,125 --> 00:20:19,000
We'll be leaving soon, too.

313
00:20:20,542 --> 00:20:21,917
That's true.

314
00:20:22,917 --> 00:20:24,625
Try calling again.

315
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:28,583
Hmm...

316
00:20:42,083 --> 00:20:45,167
This machine... I heard
it's very dangerous.

317
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:48,083
Is this machine really that dangerous?

318
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:50,875
It won't cause any trouble yet.

319
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:55,875
It will take a few more
days to fully activate.

320
00:20:55,986 --> 00:20:57,420
If this building really activates...

321
00:20:57,459 --> 00:21:01,293
Old man... can you stop
this machine now, please?

322
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:05,292
It's beyond my control now.

323
00:21:05,417 --> 00:21:07,750
The building has
already started to activate.

324
00:21:09,458 --> 00:21:11,417
Is there really no way to stop it?

325
00:21:13,875 --> 00:21:16,667
It's not entirely impossible.

326
00:21:17,792 --> 00:21:21,667
This harvester will extract the energy.

327
00:21:21,792 --> 00:21:24,768
Then it will concentrate that energy
and send it somewhere in the universe.

328
00:21:24,792 --> 00:21:28,417
So is someone else controlling
this building from somewhere else?

329
00:21:28,542 --> 00:21:30,292
I don't know where, either.

330
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:35,500
Hachi, can you find out?

331
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:38,500
This is where the landing
jammer was fired at our spaceship.

332
00:21:38,625 --> 00:21:41,083
Yes, and ship crashed because of it.

333
00:21:41,208 --> 00:21:44,250
It would be possible to track
down the location by tomorrow.

334
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,583
I have one more thing to ask, Grandpa.

335
00:21:52,167 --> 00:21:53,958
About Wooju's father...

336
00:21:54,083 --> 00:21:55,792
How did he actually die?

337
00:21:57,958 --> 00:21:59,750
Did you kill him?

338
00:22:00,083 --> 00:22:01,375
That man...

339
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:04,708
He wanted to destroy the energy
harvester the Chairman built.

340
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:07,500
It was supposed to be a secret.
I don't know how he found out.

341
00:22:07,625 --> 00:22:11,833
He even damaged the
building, causing it to go dormant.

342
00:22:11,958 --> 00:22:18,083
I had no choice but to
tell the Chairman about it.

343
00:22:18,208 --> 00:22:21,417
I really wanted to go back home as well.

344
00:22:21,542 --> 00:22:23,083
You're a really bad person.

345
00:22:23,208 --> 00:22:25,500
That's right. It's the same as killing him.

346
00:22:25,625 --> 00:22:27,625
That's why I've always
felt so sorry about it.

347
00:22:31,458 --> 00:22:34,042
Then why are you restarting this building?

348
00:22:34,167 --> 00:22:36,042
Because...

349
00:22:36,167 --> 00:22:38,875
Because of you, Your Highness.

350
00:22:39,458 --> 00:22:44,167
As long as you're in danger, the Royal Family
will definitely send someone to save you.

351
00:22:44,292 --> 00:22:47,417
Then the Chairman's
conspiracy will be exposed.

352
00:22:47,542 --> 00:22:48,542
You're crazy!

353
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:50,500
Are you putting the
prince in danger for that?

354
00:22:50,625 --> 00:22:53,333
No one has ever come to save us.

355
00:22:53,458 --> 00:22:55,500
We've been living here
for over a hundred years.

356
00:22:55,625 --> 00:22:59,583
I really... I really want to see my family.

357
00:22:59,708 --> 00:23:01,583
I really miss them.

358
00:23:13,708 --> 00:23:15,958
Air, Air!

359
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,292
Uh... Emperor?

360
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,458
Air, come here! Quickly!

361
00:23:30,583 --> 00:23:31,750
What? What's happening?

362
00:23:31,875 --> 00:23:34,000
Air, salute!
